WEBVTT

00:03.208 --> 00:06.000
Everyone has written down
their contraction word.

00:06.041 --> 00:09.542
And now we're gonna just see
if you've done it correctly.

00:09.583 --> 00:12.041
And then you will move
onto the next person.

00:12.083 --> 00:14.291
Okay, so who's first?

00:14.333 --> 00:17.583
Faith, what's another way
we can say, will not?

00:17.625 --> 00:21.083
-Won't, w-o-n-'-t.

00:21.125 --> 00:24.417
-Good girl.
Ahh, Bethany?

00:24.458 --> 00:27.000
Bethany, has not?

00:27.041 --> 00:30.917
-Hasn't, h-a-s-e-n-'-t.

00:30.959 --> 00:33.166
-That's really close.
That's really good.

00:33.208 --> 00:35.417
But we don't have an 'e' there.
But you did really good.

00:35.458 --> 00:38.166
That was so close. Almost.
So we'll just cross the 'e' out.

00:38.208 --> 00:40.834
Ah, Phillip? Can not?

00:40.875 --> 00:43.208
-Can't.

00:43.250 --> 00:46.583
C-u-n-'-t.

00:46.625 --> 00:49.917
-Yup, just need to put a
little hat on the 'u', okay?

00:49.959 --> 00:52.208
-That says c[bleep].

00:52.250 --> 00:54.333
-Okay, you know what?
That does, that's true.

00:55.583 --> 00:57.458
Okay, so we will just...
[Sound of paper ripping]

00:57.500 --> 01:00.417
That is really, really wrong.
[Sound of paper ripping]

01:00.458 --> 01:03.333
That one, we really spelled that
one wrong. Okay?

01:03.375 --> 01:05.542
-You can tell that I'm happy
when I yawn.

01:07.166 --> 01:09.709
-Okay, great. You can tell
I'm happy when the bell rings.

01:09.750 --> 01:12.458
♪ Music

01:12.500 --> 01:15.166
♪ I'm awesome, no you're
not dude, don't lie ♪

01:15.208 --> 01:17.959
♪ I'm awesome, I'm driving
around in my mom's ride ♪

01:18.000 --> 01:20.417
♪ I'm awesome, a quarter
of my life gone by ♪

01:21.709 --> 01:24.291
♪ I'm awesome ♪

01:24.333 --> 01:26.542
-[Gerry]: Listen to this.

01:26.583 --> 01:28.875
Dear Gerry. Happy
fortieth birthday.

01:28.917 --> 01:32.000
-Oh, right. Happy birthday.
-Oh, thanks buddy.

01:32.041 --> 01:34.709
This was a letter I wrote
on my thirtieth...

01:34.750 --> 01:36.959
To read to myself ten
years later.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.166
-Wow, that's adorable.
-[Gerry Reads]: You're probably

01:39.208 --> 01:42.458
sitting around the fireplace,
reading to your kids.

01:42.500 --> 01:44.542
[Laughs]: No.

01:44.583 --> 01:46.750
[Reads]: Tim, June and
little Bill Jr.

01:46.792 --> 01:48.959
Little Bill Jr. was your godson.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.834
[Reads]:First cherish your wife.
Nope, don't have one.

01:51.875 --> 01:54.458
[Reads]: Must be quite a
woman to lock you down, you dog.

01:54.500 --> 01:56.458
-[Bill laughs]

01:56.500 --> 02:00.208
-[Reads]: Secondly,
congratulations on
being a homeowner.

02:00.250 --> 02:02.583
Do we own this yet?
-Still renting.

02:02.625 --> 02:04.583
-Still renting. So that was
wrong.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.834
[Reads]: Easy feat with your
salary, Mr. Head of Phys Ed.

02:06.875 --> 02:10.417
Ahhhhh.
-Well, that's a lot of stuff you
didn't accomplish.

02:10.458 --> 02:13.750
-Guess I was a little ambitious.
-Nah, totally doable.

02:13.792 --> 02:16.250
You just didn't do it...

02:16.291 --> 02:18.583
-I kind of wasted the last
ten years of my life.

02:18.625 --> 02:20.709
-Yup, and the last three
minutes of mine. So...

02:22.959 --> 02:26.166
-Just a heads up,
Mr. Carter, the chairman
of the board of trustees,

02:26.208 --> 02:28.458
will be visiting tomorrow.
-No way!

02:28.500 --> 02:30.709
Abe's coming? I haven't
seen him in forever.

02:30.750 --> 02:32.959
Remember the bee story?
[Robert and Trudy laugh]

02:33.000 --> 02:36.125
-[Lisa laughs a little]
-[Laughs]: Oh my...the bees!

02:36.166 --> 02:38.583
[Laughs]: That was so great.
-[Laughs]: I know.

02:38.625 --> 02:41.166
-What's the bee story?
-Oh no, you definitely
had to be there.

02:41.208 --> 02:43.625
-[Robert and Trudy laugh]
-Be there!

02:43.667 --> 02:45.625
I don't think I could do it
any justice, re-telling it.

02:45.667 --> 02:49.250
So, I won't even bother.
-Anyway, he'll be spending the
afternoon.

02:49.291 --> 02:53.375
And I'm sure he'll want to see
how the school's running under
it's new leadership, so...

02:53.417 --> 02:55.792
-[Trudy laughs]: No, sorry.

02:55.834 --> 02:57.959
I was just replaying the
bee story in my head.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.291
-[Robert and Trudy laugh]
-[Robert]: Ahhh.

03:00.333 --> 03:02.709
-So, I want to impress him.
Okay?

03:02.750 --> 03:05.125
I'm thinking about a
theme day of sorts...

03:05.166 --> 03:07.625
-I'm gonna stop you right there,
with Abe, less is more.

03:07.667 --> 03:10.291
-I don't know.
-[Trudy]: No, you should
listen to Robert.

03:10.333 --> 03:13.667
Carter seems to respect him.
I don't get it either.

03:13.709 --> 03:17.375
-Trust me, quick, simple tour of
basic day-to-day operations.

03:17.417 --> 03:19.750
Maybe a bottle of scotch and
you are done.

03:19.792 --> 03:22.208
-I think I can do better
than that, Robert.

03:24.166 --> 03:26.750
-Guess I just thought I'd be
further along by now.

03:26.792 --> 03:28.834
Truth is, time flies by.

03:30.291 --> 03:32.542
And one day, you just wake up
and you realize you're closer

03:32.583 --> 03:35.041
to the end than you
are the beginning.

03:35.083 --> 03:38.500
-Ugh! Cry me a river.
-I knew you wouldn't understand.

03:38.542 --> 03:42.542
-Just because you're not married
and you don't have kids, doesn't
mean you're a huge loser.

03:42.583 --> 03:44.792
-I never said I was a huge
loser.

03:44.834 --> 03:48.667
-My uncle's forty-eight, single,
no kids, his life is amazing!

03:48.709 --> 03:50.834
Ask me where he is right now.

03:50.875 --> 03:53.500
Ask me where he is right now.

03:53.542 --> 03:55.458
-Where is he right now?

03:55.500 --> 03:58.291
-Who knows?
Thailand? Hawaii? Japan?

03:58.333 --> 04:01.291
He does whatever he wants,
whenever he wants.

04:01.333 --> 04:03.500
-Guess I am free to do
whatever I want.

04:03.542 --> 04:05.500
-There ya go, now you're
talkin'.

04:05.542 --> 04:07.750
-Maybe I am awesome and
untameable.

04:07.792 --> 04:10.667
-Yeah, like an unmarried
poor man's George Clooney.

04:10.709 --> 04:13.417
Hobo Clooney!
Bye, sir.

04:17.291 --> 04:19.750
-I guess I am kinda
Clooney-esque.

04:19.792 --> 04:22.250
-Oh, I feared this day
would come.

04:22.291 --> 04:24.542
-Where is the rat?
-Esteban is a ferret.

04:24.583 --> 04:28.125
A beautiful, tender ferret
who's now gone missing.

04:28.166 --> 04:30.417
-Makes no difference
in the dark.

04:30.458 --> 04:32.917
-We gotta find him.
Not to raise any alarms,

04:32.959 --> 04:36.083
but there may have been
some spills around his cage.

04:36.125 --> 04:38.500
-What sort of "Spills"?

04:38.542 --> 04:42.625
-Well, let's just say Esteban
might be a scootch radioactive.

04:42.667 --> 04:44.625
-[Sound of pitter patter
in the ceiling]

04:44.667 --> 04:47.875
-Oh yeah, that is definitely not
a normal pitter patter speed.

04:47.917 --> 04:52.208
-At last. A worthy adversary.

04:53.000 --> 04:55.500
-Wait...What's that?

04:55.542 --> 04:57.709
-It says it's edible.
-I'd eat anything

04:57.750 --> 05:01.208
-[Gerry snaps his fingers]
-[Laughs]: Yeah ya would.

05:01.250 --> 05:03.583
-Ahh, it's a big day today,
isn't it?

05:03.625 --> 05:06.667
-Yeah! Paul finally gets to
move back into his house.

05:06.709 --> 05:08.667
-[Dwyer]: Hey, where I lay my
hat, that's my home.

05:08.709 --> 05:11.458
-[Claps]: Ya done?
Today's my birthday.

05:11.500 --> 05:14.125
That's what I wanted to say,
it's the big 4-0.
-Oh, congratulations.

05:14.166 --> 05:16.333
-[Bobbi]: Oh!
-Forty!?

05:16.375 --> 05:18.625
-Yeah, I don't look it. Yeah.
-That's a biggie.

05:18.667 --> 05:21.500
-Yeah, you are super old!
-[Bobbi and Trudy laugh]

05:21.542 --> 05:24.500
-You're old. You look like
a thousand. So...

05:24.542 --> 05:28.500
Wouldn't talk. Anyway, age is
meaningless when your life is
amazing!

05:28.542 --> 05:31.625
-Oh, we'll it must be pretty
meaningful to you then.

05:31.667 --> 05:33.625
-[Bobbi snickers]
-[Gerry]: That's funny.

05:33.667 --> 05:36.542
So, what is the plan for
this evening then?

05:36.583 --> 05:40.542
-[Dwyer]: I got the big move.
-Yeah and I have a new shower
head, so I'm pretty booked.

05:40.583 --> 05:42.750
[Bobbi laughs]
-[Gerry]: Ah, wasn't talking
about you guys.

05:42.792 --> 05:46.667
Nisha! What is the
plan then, Nisha?

05:46.709 --> 05:49.583
-I'm actually checking out
this new club with some of
my friends.

05:49.625 --> 05:54.000
We like to get together once a
month and just check out like
a new hot spot in the...

05:54.041 --> 05:56.291
-I'm in.
-Really?

05:56.333 --> 05:59.125
-Sure, I'll go.
-Oh, this is going to be so fun!

05:59.166 --> 06:02.417
-Okay, so pre-drinks
chez moi at eleven!
-[Nisha squeals excited]

06:02.458 --> 06:04.792
-I love chez moi. Don't know
where it is, but I'll find it.

06:04.834 --> 06:07.083
-Sounds fun.
Maybe I'll join.

06:07.125 --> 06:09.291
-[Laughs]: Stop it.

06:09.333 --> 06:11.500
I mean, I'm a tiny bit
older than Nisha. But...

06:11.542 --> 06:14.750
[Laughs]: I think you're gonna
feel really out of place.

06:14.792 --> 06:18.333
-Or maybe I'll just boot your
man berries up into your
nasal cavity.

06:18.375 --> 06:20.542
-[Clears throat]

06:22.667 --> 06:27.125
♪ Music

06:27.166 --> 06:29.375
-A little higher on the left.

06:29.417 --> 06:31.583
It's supposed to resemble an X,
you guys.

06:31.625 --> 06:34.041
-Last minute fun fair,
impressive.

06:34.083 --> 06:38.250
-Well, it took a little creative
logistics. But, I'm a doer.

06:38.291 --> 06:40.667
-Really going above and
beyond on this thing, huh?

06:40.709 --> 06:43.083
-I want Mr. Carter to know that
the school's in good hands.

06:44.875 --> 06:48.959
-Aren't you a bit worried that
frivolous expenditures send
a questionable message?

06:49.000 --> 06:53.041
-That's why I'm not spending
frivolously on, say, a bottle
of scotch.

06:53.083 --> 06:57.583
-That was a hundred bucks.
What'd this run us? A thousand?

06:57.625 --> 06:59.667
Two grand?

07:00.667 --> 07:03.291
Twenty five hund...Oh my gosh!

07:03.333 --> 07:05.625
-Obviously not.
-Oh.

07:06.208 --> 07:08.667
-It was more like three.

07:08.709 --> 07:11.834
[Exhales, clears throat]

07:11.875 --> 07:15.291
-Hey!
-Hey Ger, oh my God,
you look amazing!

07:15.333 --> 07:18.500
So Berlin, I love it! Yeah.
-Hey, when did this place open?

07:18.542 --> 07:21.417
-Oh no, it's a pop up, so it
hasn't been here very long.

07:21.458 --> 07:25.542
-A what?
-[Laughs]: Oh my God,
you're hilarious. Come on.

07:25.583 --> 07:28.500
-Oh yeah, okay. Hey guys.
Alright.

07:28.542 --> 07:30.458
-[Nisha]: These are my friends.
-Oh.

07:30.500 --> 07:33.166
-The one in the blue deals
drugs.
-[Gerry]: Why is there no music?

07:33.208 --> 07:35.583
People are dancing to nothing,
there's no music playing.

07:35.625 --> 07:38.208
-That's what these are for.
It's a silent disco.

07:38.250 --> 07:40.834
So you hear the music
through your headphones.

07:40.875 --> 07:44.125
-What's the point of this?
-Oh it's huge, everybody's
doing it everywhere.

07:44.166 --> 07:46.375
-Oh is it? Okay.
-It's the new thing.

07:46.417 --> 07:49.083
Brooklyn, Europe, New York.
-Oh, Europe.

07:49.125 --> 07:51.333
-Places.
-Let's do it.

07:51.375 --> 07:53.625
-Okay, ahhh! Let's go!
-[Gerry laughs]

07:53.667 --> 07:56.500
[People chatter]

07:56.542 --> 07:58.875
[People chatter]

07:58.917 --> 08:01.792
-This is so fun!
[♪ Dance music from headphones]

08:01.834 --> 08:04.667
Hey, how do you turn these down?
It's so loud. It's too loud.

08:04.709 --> 08:08.458
-No, no. It's the whole thing,
you don't turn it down Gerry.
Come on!

08:08.500 --> 08:10.458
-No it's too loud.
-Hey! Good, you came!

08:10.500 --> 08:12.750
-Yeah, I wouldn't miss this.
[♪ Dance music from headphones]

08:12.792 --> 08:15.542
-Just 'cause you're a cougar,
doesn't mean you have to
dress like one.

08:15.583 --> 08:17.500
-Oh really, Pinocchio?

08:17.542 --> 08:20.375
Just 'cause you're a bonehead,
doesn't mean you have to dress
like one.

08:20.417 --> 08:22.625
-It's called the Berlin look,
by the way.

08:22.667 --> 08:24.625
-[Trudy laughs]

08:24.667 --> 08:26.917
-How do ya...?

08:26.959 --> 08:29.166
-That's dirty!

08:29.208 --> 08:33.291
-[Gerry sighs]
[♪ Dance music from headphones]

08:33.333 --> 08:35.667
-Hi.
-Hi.

08:35.709 --> 08:38.959
-You wouldn't happen to be
Jackie's dad, would you?

08:39.000 --> 08:40.959
'Cause she's puking in the
bathroom.

08:42.250 --> 08:45.625
-I think you probably thought
I was Jackie's brother.

08:45.667 --> 08:47.583
And no.

08:50.917 --> 08:53.083
-What time does this
place close?

08:53.125 --> 08:56.458
Two AM, but don't worry we're
going to go to an after hours
barcade!

08:56.500 --> 08:58.709
-Okay, I got nowhere to go!
-[Nisha]: Right?

08:58.750 --> 09:01.375
-Awesome, yeah! No ball and
chain for this guy.

09:01.417 --> 09:03.583
-Get the...
-[Gerry]: Oh yeah, yeah.

09:03.625 --> 09:06.208
-Keep 'em on!
Mmm, mmm

09:06.250 --> 09:08.834
[Nisha]: Whhhooosh.

09:08.875 --> 09:11.500
-Let me get a drink.
-Anything! Everything!

09:11.542 --> 09:13.667
[♪ Dance music from headphones]
-Are you running out of steam?

09:13.709 --> 09:15.959
[♪ Dance music from headphones]

09:16.000 --> 09:19.333
-Yes, I am. Okay?
-Yeah me too! I hate this place.

09:19.375 --> 09:22.291
What's wrong with these people?
-I gotta keep going here, Trudy.

09:22.333 --> 09:24.709
'Cause this is who I am now,
this is me.

09:24.750 --> 09:28.125
-Yeah, well I've a reputation to
uphold so I'm not goin'
anywhere.

09:28.166 --> 09:30.542
-Let's make the best of
a bad situation.

09:30.583 --> 09:32.542
Who ya dancing' with?
-Oh shut up.

09:32.583 --> 09:35.500
-Nobody, okay. Alright.

09:35.542 --> 09:39.208
-Isn't this great? It's like
you're not even forty.

09:39.250 --> 09:42.375
You're just normal for once!

09:42.417 --> 09:45.458
Ffffshh.
Yes!

09:45.500 --> 09:48.458
Watch out for the little one,
she steals.

09:48.500 --> 09:51.500
-Ha ha.
-Cool! Par-tay!

09:57.542 --> 10:01.792
-Oh, will ya get off?

10:03.166 --> 10:05.709
Ugh, sorry!
Thank you.

10:07.500 --> 10:10.125
[Takes a deep breath]:
That's my uncle.

10:10.166 --> 10:13.041
[♪ Music]
-[Gerry]: Oh.

10:14.625 --> 10:16.625
Thank you. Okay let's go.

10:20.583 --> 10:24.000
-Hey, Jasmine!
-Gerry!

10:24.041 --> 10:26.291
-Oh!
-Hey, how's the ankle?

10:26.333 --> 10:28.792
-Good, thanks to you.
Saved my life!

10:28.834 --> 10:31.625
-Nah.
-I'd be dead if it wasn't
for you.

10:31.667 --> 10:33.917
Hey BJ!

10:33.959 --> 10:36.333
Wow, what are the odds of
running into you twice in
two weeks?

10:36.375 --> 10:38.333
-Oh, we live upstairs. So...

10:38.375 --> 10:40.667
-Live upstairs? And I live
around the corner.

10:40.709 --> 10:43.542
But the odds of us meeting here,
fate!
-[Jasmine laughs]

10:43.583 --> 10:45.792
-Mooom!
-Just a second, BJ.

10:45.834 --> 10:48.750
Um, I am sorry that I
never got in touch.

10:48.792 --> 10:51.291
Your email kept bouncing back.
-What did you have as my email?

10:51.333 --> 10:55.291
-Gerry underscore Duncan aka...

10:55.333 --> 10:59.417
-No, it's gerry underscore
duncan underscore aka mrd.

10:59.458 --> 11:02.208
-Ahhh.
-Gerry underscore duncan
aka mrd was taken.

11:02.250 --> 11:04.417
-Sorry.
-Anyway, that happens.

11:04.458 --> 11:07.542
-Mooom!
-Bill Jr., that's enough.

11:07.583 --> 11:10.291
-Sorry...Ahhh...

11:10.333 --> 11:12.583
Bill Jr? That's what BJ
stands for?

11:12.625 --> 11:14.417
-Yeah.

11:15.375 --> 11:18.583
-[Quietly]: Oh my God. Bill.
Here we go.

11:18.625 --> 11:21.333
-We have a fair today at our
school and you're coming.

11:21.375 --> 11:23.667
He would love it.
You would love it.

11:23.709 --> 11:26.542
-Today, ahhh...
What do I have today.

11:26.583 --> 11:28.959
[Jasmine]: Today is...
-There's gonna be a bouncy
castle.

11:29.041 --> 11:31.291
And a dunk tank!!
-I want to go to the fair!

11:31.333 --> 11:33.333
-[Laughs]: Yeah? I bet you do.

11:33.375 --> 11:36.291
Okay, you know what? Today
actually works. BJ loves fairs.

11:36.333 --> 11:38.792
-See ya this afternoon. Alright.
-[Jasmine]: Okay, bye.

11:38.834 --> 11:41.834
-It's about yay long.
Face like a little raccoon.

11:41.875 --> 11:44.583
Body like a...
I wanna say hair snake.

11:44.625 --> 11:47.208
-Sounds like a monster.
-Oh no, Esteban's super cute.

11:47.250 --> 11:50.208
Adorable little ball of almost
certain nuclear decay.

11:50.250 --> 11:53.250
I miss him.
-At the end of the day...

11:53.291 --> 11:55.792
Only one of us will survive!

11:55.834 --> 11:59.875
-Seems a little extreme. I was
thinking just a twist tie on his
cage door from now on.

11:59.917 --> 12:02.250
-[Ferret squeaks]

12:02.291 --> 12:04.291
-[Ferret squeaks]

12:04.333 --> 12:06.625
-It's go time.

12:06.667 --> 12:10.709
Alba gu bràth!!!!!

12:10.750 --> 12:14.125
-[Simon yells]:
You'll kill him!!! Esteban!!!

12:16.000 --> 12:18.375
-Oh, Mr. Carter.
I'm Principal Mason.

12:18.417 --> 12:20.375
It is so nice to finally
meet you.

12:20.417 --> 12:22.583
-Ah haha, call the cops!
-[Mr. Carter laughs]

12:22.625 --> 12:25.291
-Who let this son of a
gun in here? Abe!
-[Mr. Carter laughs]

12:25.333 --> 12:27.375
-Or should I say babe?
You look fantastic!

12:27.417 --> 12:30.041
-Lookin' pretty good yourself,
Robert.
-Please...Go on!

12:30.083 --> 12:32.500
-[Robert and Mr. Carter laugh]
-Robert what happened to your...

12:32.542 --> 12:34.709
Hawaiian shirts and your
sandals?
[Laughs]

12:34.750 --> 12:36.959
-I feel like we're in hug
territory.
-Yeah!

12:37.000 --> 12:39.917
-It's been a minute, hasn't it?
Ohh, pour some sugar on me.
-[Mr. Carter]: Ohh!

12:39.959 --> 12:42.208
-If memory serves, I think
you'll enjoy this.

12:42.250 --> 12:44.917
-Oh, this is above and beyond.
-[Robert]: Your favourite kind,
as I recall.

12:44.959 --> 12:47.125
-[Mr. Carter]: Thank you.
-You're most welcome.

12:47.166 --> 12:51.875
-You know what else is above
and beyond? This fair that I
organized in your honour.

12:51.917 --> 12:54.250
-Mmm.
-Wait 'til you see what
this one did.

12:54.291 --> 12:56.250
She really outdid herself.

12:56.291 --> 13:00.542
-You know, I always love to see
new principals taking
initiative.

13:00.583 --> 13:02.834
-[Exhales]: Thank you.
-Shall we?

13:02.875 --> 13:05.291
-[Mr. Carter]: Thank you, Sir.
-[Mr. Carter and Robert laugh]

13:05.333 --> 13:07.333
[♪ Carnival music]

13:07.375 --> 13:09.583
[Bobbi]: What the f...?
Oh!

13:09.625 --> 13:12.375
I think what it is is the
teaching keeps me young.

13:12.417 --> 13:14.375
-Oh.
-Guess how old I am?

13:14.417 --> 13:16.959
-I don't know. Forty-ish?
-Oh, that's flattering.

13:17.000 --> 13:19.166
Actually, I just turned forty.
-Oh.

13:19.208 --> 13:22.500
-I assume by forty-ish you meant
the lower end of the forties.

13:22.542 --> 13:25.208
-You know, I wasn't sure about
you at first, but you're funny.

13:25.250 --> 13:28.750
-Oh, careful Bill Jr. He's okay?
-Oh, he's fine. Kids will be
kids, Gerry.

13:28.792 --> 13:31.542
-Okay, alright. Ahh, it's good
to see you're not smothering
your kid.

13:31.583 --> 13:34.875
A lot of parents do that.
-Scared kids become
scared adults.

13:34.917 --> 13:37.083
I want him to learn to take
risks.

13:37.125 --> 13:40.000
-[Gerry]:So you're a risk taker?
-Seize the day, you know?

13:40.041 --> 13:43.041
Carpe diem.
-[Gerry whispers]: Carpe diem.

13:43.083 --> 13:44.834
-Oh God. Excuse me.
-Okay.

13:46.875 --> 13:50.291
-The great thing about Xavier
Academy is we're all just one
big happy family.

13:50.333 --> 13:52.792
-Mmm hmm.
-I like to organize events like

13:52.834 --> 13:56.417
this to encourage school spirit.
-What a wonderful idea.

13:56.458 --> 13:59.417
-[Quietly]: Guess less isn't
more, huh? More is more.

13:59.458 --> 14:02.375
-Well, couldn't be more happy
to say I was wrong.

14:02.417 --> 14:04.750
-[Dwyer]: How's everybody doing?
-[Jasmine and Gerry]: Yeah!

14:04.792 --> 14:07.417
-[Dwyer]: Firstly, I wanna
introduce the band.
-[Robert]: Nice work.

14:07.458 --> 14:09.917
These guys have been working
so hard at this. This is their
first gig.

14:09.959 --> 14:12.417
I remember the day they came
and said to me they wanted to
start a band.

14:12.458 --> 14:15.417
I told them it was going to be
a lot of work. But that they
should go for it.

14:15.458 --> 14:18.583
Nobody likes to look back and
wonder in life, what could have
happened.

14:18.625 --> 14:20.792
-Seize the day.
-[Dwyer]: This is their moment.

14:20.834 --> 14:23.125
Got this number for you guys.
-[Gerry]: Seize the day.

14:23.166 --> 14:25.250
-I know you guys are gonna
enjoy it.
-[Gerry]: Seize the day.

14:25.291 --> 14:28.041
Could I steal that?
-Oh Gerry, no.

14:28.083 --> 14:30.667
-[Gerry]: Mr. Dwyer everybody.
The band. Thank you.

14:30.709 --> 14:33.417
Hope you're having a great day
at our school.

14:33.458 --> 14:36.083
Where's Jasmine? Ja...?

14:36.125 --> 14:39.000
Jasmine.
Jasmine everybody .

14:39.041 --> 14:42.000
I've done more soul searching
in the last three minutes

14:42.041 --> 14:44.417
than I have in the last forty
years, 'cause of you.

14:44.458 --> 14:46.834
This girl. First of all,
she saved my life.

14:46.875 --> 14:50.000
Then you named your son
after my roommate, Bill.

14:50.041 --> 14:52.291
Coincidentally. Those are
signs, Jasmine.

14:52.333 --> 14:55.750
The universe is talking to us.
-They're saying get off the
stage!

14:55.792 --> 14:59.375
-[Laughs]: Oh!
-Shut up Trudy! Shut up!

14:59.417 --> 15:01.417
[Gerry]: Not right now.

15:02.375 --> 15:04.917
Sorry.
Carpe Diem.

15:04.959 --> 15:08.208
Carpe Diem. Those are the
three words you taught me.

15:08.250 --> 15:11.208
For those of you that don't
know, that is Latin for...

15:11.250 --> 15:14.083
-The milk is sour.
-Would you just shut up?!

15:16.000 --> 15:18.333
Seize the day. Seize the day.

15:18.375 --> 15:20.667
You taught me that.

15:20.709 --> 15:22.959
-Would you like to see
the gymnasium?

15:23.000 --> 15:26.083
-No, I'm enjoying this.
-You taught me that.

15:26.125 --> 15:29.291
-[Light crackles and sparks]
-So, do you Jasmine...

15:29.333 --> 15:31.959
[Sound of fire spreading]

15:34.375 --> 15:37.166
-Would you do me the honour?
Take my hand in marriage.

15:39.125 --> 15:42.083
[Fire spreading, beam falls]

15:42.125 --> 15:45.083
-Just ignore that. Ignore that.
-Oh my God!

15:45.125 --> 15:48.333
[Fire spreading]
-Really?

15:48.375 --> 15:50.291
-Ohh! Ah!

15:51.250 --> 15:53.417
-[Ferret squeaks]
[Simon]: Esteban!

15:53.458 --> 15:57.709
-[Crowd screaming]
-[Lisa]: No, no, no, no, no.
It's not what it looks like.

15:57.750 --> 16:00.375
-Jasmine?
-For the love of God!

16:00.417 --> 16:02.333
[Lisa cries]: No, no.
-Well?

16:02.375 --> 16:05.125
-No.
-You said you took risks.

16:05.166 --> 16:07.291
I took a risk, this is a
big risk.

16:07.333 --> 16:09.500
-I'm gonna go call the fire
department.

16:09.542 --> 16:11.959
-[Lisa breathes heavily, upset]

16:12.000 --> 16:14.333
-[Simon screams]:
Don't hurt him!

16:14.375 --> 16:16.834
-[Siren approaching]
-[Lisa cries]

16:16.875 --> 16:19.333
-[Ferret squeaks]
-[Sirens get louder]

16:20.458 --> 16:23.458
Mr. Carter, I cannot tell you
how sorry I am.

16:23.500 --> 16:26.208
I mean, I would never
intentionally allow such

16:26.250 --> 16:28.625
a racially insensitive image
at Xavier.

16:28.667 --> 16:32.000
Exactly. And I am not racist.

16:32.041 --> 16:36.208
Far from it. In fact, I sponsor
three children from Africa.

16:36.250 --> 16:38.458
I mean they tried to send me
some South Americans, and I was

16:38.500 --> 16:41.208
like I want three from Africa,
thank you very much.

16:41.250 --> 16:43.792
Maybe one day this can
be our little bee story.

16:43.834 --> 16:48.125
-[Mouths]: No! No!
-Because you have that story
about the bees?

16:48.166 --> 16:51.208
-[Phone clicks, dial tone]
-Hello?

16:51.250 --> 16:53.792
He hung up on me.
-Carter hates the bee story.

16:53.834 --> 16:56.250
-You said it was funny though!
-Well to me it is.

16:56.291 --> 16:58.458
To him, it's a horrifically
scarring memory.

16:58.500 --> 17:00.709
Do you want to know what
happened?

17:00.750 --> 17:04.959
He went to a yoga class,
outdoors and a bee stung
him right on the...

17:05.000 --> 17:09.250
-Okay Robert.
-...Bees-nus. And he cried
like a little bee-yotch.

17:09.291 --> 17:11.375
-I get it, Robert.

17:13.375 --> 17:15.875
-Where are you going with
his bottle of scotch?

17:15.917 --> 17:19.542
-Mr. Carter, said that I need
it more than he does.

17:19.583 --> 17:22.083
-[Laughs]: Oh!

17:22.125 --> 17:25.375
-I searched the grounds.
Esteban's nowhere to be found.

17:27.000 --> 17:28.667
Goodbye, sweet prince.

17:29.709 --> 17:32.875
-Esteban is the government's
problem now.

17:32.917 --> 17:35.125
-Honestly, he's not anyone's
problem.

17:35.166 --> 17:37.667
He's a domesticated ferret.
He couldn't win a fight against
a chipmunk.

17:37.709 --> 17:39.959
He'll be dead by sunrise.

17:40.000 --> 17:42.375
Well, guess it's just you and
me now, Juan Pedro.

17:44.125 --> 17:46.291
[Simon]: Juan Pedro?

17:46.834 --> 17:49.458
Oh no!
-Let's...

17:49.500 --> 17:51.917
Rock and roll.

17:51.959 --> 17:56.250
-Okay.
Hey, hey wait! Okay.

17:56.291 --> 17:58.917
♪ Bar music
-[Bill laughs]: Let me get
this straight.

17:58.959 --> 18:01.375
You proposed on a first date?

18:01.417 --> 18:03.625
-It's not funny.
-It's pretty funny.

18:03.667 --> 18:06.417
-Technically it wasn't on a
first date, 'cause I had
already seen her.

18:06.458 --> 18:09.375
It was like, the third time I'd
seen her. This first time,
she saved my life.

18:09.417 --> 18:12.125
And that's worth about ten dates
when you save someone's life.

18:12.166 --> 18:14.333
-Maybe you should write a letter
to fifty year old Gerry,

18:14.375 --> 18:16.375
explaining what not to do
on a first date.

18:16.417 --> 18:19.333
-I'm telling you, that fire
ruined it. If there was no fire,
she woulda said yes.

18:19.375 --> 18:22.000
-She absolutely woulda said no.
-Why would you say that?

18:22.041 --> 18:24.709
-Hey, Lisa.
-No, no, no, no.

18:26.208 --> 18:29.041
-This isn't really a BYOB sort
of place.

18:29.083 --> 18:31.291
-A guy...
-So call the cops.

18:31.333 --> 18:34.291
-A guy was just drinking out
of that with a moustache. So...

18:34.333 --> 18:37.667
-Okay, I am going to make an
exception this one...

18:37.709 --> 18:40.834
Okay, alright.
-Ugh.

18:40.875 --> 18:44.250
[Smells cooler]

18:44.291 --> 18:46.250
Oh, what a difference. I don't
know how you drink that.

18:46.291 --> 18:48.625
-[Lisa sighs]: I thought
I was moving up in life.

18:48.667 --> 18:51.250
I was doing so well.

18:52.417 --> 18:55.333
And you just managed to
ruin everything.

18:55.375 --> 18:57.834
-Ha. Whatever.

18:57.875 --> 19:02.333
You're not moving up in life,
you're still a sad woman with
too many cats.

19:02.375 --> 19:05.917
-Well at least I'm not a forty
year old, living in a rental

19:05.959 --> 19:08.333
with a grown man roommate.

19:08.375 --> 19:10.750
It's pretty pathetic.
-[Gerry]: Fair enough.

19:10.792 --> 19:13.750
A toast to us.
-Whatever.

19:13.792 --> 19:16.333
-Whatever. Whatever to you.

19:17.250 --> 19:21.250
-Ahh. Oh that burns!
[Clears throat]

19:21.291 --> 19:24.500
Whoo.
[Lisa sighs]

19:24.542 --> 19:26.792
-Alright, you know it's 4:30,
you might wanna just...

19:26.834 --> 19:30.375
-You might just wanna shut up.
Okay? Just shut up, Gerry.

19:30.417 --> 19:32.750
-Alright.
-[Takes a deep breath]

19:32.792 --> 19:35.625
-Ya threw a little KKK rally, so
you're a little bit disturbed.

19:35.667 --> 19:38.250
-Oh my God, I wanna hurt you
so bad.

19:38.291 --> 19:41.125
-Makes sense. Makes sense.
I would do that too if I was...

19:41.166 --> 19:44.125
-[Lisa takes a deep breath]
-A big KKK supporter.

19:44.166 --> 19:47.542
Yeah, that was timed well.
Good job.

19:50.792 --> 19:54.333
[Sound of cats purring]

19:54.375 --> 19:57.750
[Sound of cats purring]

19:57.792 --> 20:00.583
-Ahh! What?!

20:00.625 --> 20:02.250
-Noooo!

20:03.125 --> 20:05.625
-What's goin' on?
Oh my head.

20:05.667 --> 20:08.291
-Noooo.
-Oh God.

20:08.333 --> 20:10.417
-Noooo. Ahh!
-Ahh! Ahh!

20:10.458 --> 20:12.625
-Ahhh.

20:12.667 --> 20:14.959
-[Gerry]: We got married! Ahh!
-[Lisa]: Ahhhh.

20:15.000 --> 20:17.834
-Ohhh!
-What? What the...?!

20:17.875 --> 20:20.125
-My bridesmaid.
-No! What's that cat?

20:20.166 --> 20:22.333
-[Cat purrs and meows]
-[Lisa]: Ring bearer.

20:22.375 --> 20:24.625
-You've got to be kidding me.

20:24.667 --> 20:27.041
Oh no! Oh no!

20:27.083 --> 20:29.291
-No.
-Mmmm.

20:29.333 --> 20:31.750
-What else happened?

20:31.792 --> 20:34.792
-I don't know. Ah.
[Throws up]

20:34.834 --> 20:38.208
-[Cat meows]
-[Lisa]: I'm sorry Mittens.
-[Gerry and Lisa groan]

20:38.250 --> 20:41.959
[♪ Music]
-Move over.
-Ah. Oh I just puked on my cat.

20:44.041 --> 20:45.041
Okay, come on. We're up.

20:45.083 --> 20:47.208
-[Lisa slurs]: We're getting
married.

20:47.250 --> 20:49.417
-Two for marriage,
non-smoking.

20:49.458 --> 20:51.709
-[Lisa laughs]
-[Gerry laughs]: Four!

20:51.750 --> 20:53.917
Four for marriage.
-Four!

20:53.959 --> 20:56.709
-We like them. They can't
sign the documents.
-No.

20:56.750 --> 21:00.083
-You don't turn them away,
that's allowed now.
-Yeah.
